Project 06

Description

I have given all of you feedback for your final project proposals, and this assignment is meant to be a first step in service of your final project, and an (optional) chance to build your skills in the javascript libraries weve covered: d3 or plotly. Follow the directions in my feedback and create some preliminary graphs for your final project.

I encourage all students to attempt to attempt to use javascript. Even if you are not planning on using these tools for your final project, the exercise can be used to build your skills above our basic assignments in project 5. Since this is in service of your final project however, projects submitted in either dash or shiny will be accepted if thats what youll be using.

Multi Agency Permits.

Mayors Office of Data Analytics

  • Multi Agency Permits in NYC (Visualization).

Department of Buildings work permits are required for most construction projects. If the projects scope requires plans and permits, you must hire a New York State licensed professional engineer (PE) or registered architect (RA).

Data Gathering

The data will be provided by the Mayors Office of Data Analytics.

Link: http://www1.nyc.gov/site/analytics/index.page

Data source: Socrata (24as-fxn4)

  • Link: https://data.cityofnewyork.us/City-Government/Multi-Agency-Permits/xfyi-uyt5.

  • Developer Link: https://dev.socrata.com/foundry/data.cityofnewyork.us/24as-fxn4.
